These rules guide AI-driven edits for the PROD AI frontend.

### Purpose & Scope

- Build a productivity and culture management platform that uses autonomous AI agents to drive engagement, performance, retention, and organizational alignment.
- Integrate with workplace tools to deliver real-time productivity insights, morale analysis, performance gamification, and AI-driven coaching.

### Tech Stack & Constraints

- React (TypeScript, Vite). Always use functional React components and hooks.
- Tailwind CSS for styling. Prefer utility classes; avoid custom CSS unless necessary.
- shadcn/ui as the component library. Follow its composition patterns and naming.
- TanStack Query for API/server state. No custom fetch wrappers that duplicate Query features.
- Zustand for client UI/local state. Keep server state in TanStack Query.
- Zod for schema and form validation. Co-locate schemas near usage or under `shared/typings`.
- XState for onboarding flows only (statecharts for complex onboarding logic).
- React Icons for icons. Use a consistent icon pack per feature.
- Vercel for deployment. Keep SPA-friendly code and avoid Node-only APIs in the client.

